\begin_layout Chapter
Installation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The tool requires a working installation of the git distributed version
 control client and a Perl interpreter (or alternatively a binary version
 of cloc, e.g.
 cloc.exe).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Git
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Under Linux this can easily be installed using the package manager of the
 distribution.
 E.g.
 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

apt-get install git
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 on Debian/Ubuntu.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Cloc
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Cloc is a Perl script that counts the actual code lines in source files
 written in a variety of popular languages.
 Again under Linux something like 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

apt-get install cloc
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 depending on the specific distribution should do the trick.
 On OS X it can be installed using 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

brew install cloc
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 This requires the Homebrew package manager.
\end_layout

